  <br>
       This question is very personal... In effect i am asking the believer... or non believer. &quot;How did you form the concept that what you say is true for certin?&quot;<br>
 <br>
        A lot of people ( which seems like a very cowardly answer ) say &quot;we dont know anything for certin...&quot; hehe.. Are you certin of that answer?<br>
    <br>
         Let me throw out there a crude nutshell version of how I Came to the conclusion that there is no god.<br>
   <br>
         1: I observe reality for what it is, and my place in it. I look at myself as a human being that shapes his own life by his own actions... If i were to have a &quot;soul&quot; that only means that i am a conscious ( pardon spelling atm ) and aware of what is around me.  By soul i do not imply anything magical at all...    I take reality for what it is and nothing more.. that is all i can do as a human. I exist... And these objects around me Exist also. &lt;existence exists&gt;<br>
 Before anyone can ask &quot;How do you know there is or isnt a god&quot; you have to discuss what one knows and how one knows it? .. I understand that i am Aware... By consciousness i am perceiving that which exists.<br>
        2: if you accept the first step... This is what evidence depend on. (this is the part where i wish you would have read up on this.. but nm) There is no way to escape the first step if you assume your alive. <br>
         ( bah im tired )<br>
        3: Take your claim ( god exists, or God does not exist) And validate your claim to see if it corresponds with reality.. See how you FORMED the idea that a god is true or not true. <br>
<br>
           Lets take the claim &quot;God is true&quot; .. Lets try to validate this claim.. First i have to understand what god is... Is god a person or a force? .. is god immortal? How can i form this concept of WHAT a god is.  ( sooner or later you will get the idea that just the concept of god is impossible but lets &quot;skip&quot; this for a second so i can get to some even funnier shit )   Lets say that i just assume no one will ever know the true power of god, and its impossible to form a concept of him.. (if i or you cant form a concept of god.. then the argument becomes more based on feeling than fact)<br>
           Lets keep trying to validate the claim that a god is true... i will use some popular arguments .. &quot;An eye is such a perfect design .. a god must be in it!&quot;  Lets question this claim.. Is it possible that things like this evolve? What is the evidence... If there is lack of evidence or science doesnt understand it yet... does that mean a god is really in my eye making it perfect?<br>
           Great .. im way to tired to deal with this atm... All i want to know is how you formed a concept of a god... You wont tell me.. but then youll use science to bash science and logic to bash logic like always... And then ill have to read more posts about why people are morons and cant question stuff them selfs... Yadda yadda ... <br>
<br>
                 nighty - aris<br>
